  <h3>Inline</h3>
  <p>Inline alerts can be placed in a container or a component and shouldn’t block other content. The required elements include a bar or a border, an icon, a title, and a container. Text that provides more information about the alert may or may not be included. Sometimes a close button is required if an inline alert needs to be dismissible.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
    <img src="http://www.placehold.it/800x600" />
  {%- endcall %}

  {% call components.example(palette='darkest') %}
    <img src="http://www.placehold.it/800x600" />
  {%- endcall %}

  <p>The alternate inline alert style features a border instead of a horizontal line on top which is used to express more urgency or to grab the attention of a user.</p>

  <h3>Toast</h3>
  <p>Toast alerts slide into view in the top right corner of the page and rest on top of content. The required elements include a bar, an icon, a title, a close button, and a white container with a drop shadow. Text that provides more information about the alert may or may not be included.</p>

