{% call components.section("Usage") -%}
  <p>Alerts are notifications that appear or are generated to communicate with users.</p>

  <h3>Inline</h3>
  <p>Use to present simple information or a local notification, like after a user submits a form with errors. Inline alerts should be informational or identify any actions that are required before a user can continue. They should also have the option to be dismissible.<p>

  <h3>Toast</h3>
  <p>Use to present a notification about an important global event or a change. Toast alerts shouldn’t interrupt a user’s workflow therefore they should always be dismissible.</p>

  <h3>Severity</h3>
  <p>Severity communicates the urgency of an alert. The combination of a status icon, a title, and the container style all help to clarify severity levels of alerts.</p>

