{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}
  <h3>Stacking</h3>
  <p>If the same alert variant appears in the same area, they stack. The most recent alert should appear at the top of the stack and push other alerts down. When stacked alerts are dismissed or time out, the remaining alerts will move up and fill the empty space.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="multi-column--min-300-wide margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="http://www.placehold.it/800x600" />
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h3>Responsive design</h3>
  <p>On small screens, both alert variants will span the full column and be positioned in the center of the layout. Toast alerts will continue to stack on top of each other, so be mindful of how much vertical space the group will occupy if there are multiple alerts.</p>

{%- endcall %}

